  .then((user) => console.log(user))
  .catch((error) => console.error('Failed to fetch user:', error));
```

In this code snippet, the function `findUniqueUser` attempts to retrieve a user from the database based on a given username using the `findFirst()` method. If a user is found, it is returned; otherwise, an error is thrown. This method is particularly useful when querying a database where uniqueness constraints are applied.

