In JavaScript, a number is considered prime if it is greater than 1 and has no divisors other than 1 and itself. To determine if a number is prime, one can use the following method:

```javascript
// Function to check if a number is prime
function isPrime(num) {
  // Check if the number is less than 2
  if (num <= 1) {
    return false;
  }
  // Check for factors from 2 to the square root of num
  for (let i = 2; i <= Math.sqrt(num); i++) {
    if (num % i === 0) {
      return false; // If a factor is found, num is not prime
    }
  }
  return true; // If no factors are found, num is prime
}
```

This function takes a number as input and returns `true` if the number is prime, and `false` otherwise. It first checks if the number is less than or equal to 1, in which case it returns `false` since numbers less than 2 are not prime. Then, it iterates from 2 up to the square root of the number (using `Math.sqrt(num)`) to check for any divisors. If any divisor is found, it returns `false`. If no divisors are found, it concludes that the number is prime and returns `true`. This method is efficient because it only needs to check divisibility up to the square root of the number, rather than checking all numbers up to the number itself.

В C# для отправки HTTP-запросов, включая POST-запросы, обычно используется класс `HttpWebRequest` или `HttpClient`.

### Пример использования `HttpWebRequest` для отправки POST-запроса:

```csharp
using System;
using System.IO;
using System.Net;
using System.Text;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        string url = "http://example.com/api";
        string jsonPayload = "{\"name\":\"John\", \"age\":\"30\"}";

        HttpWebRequest request = (HttpWebRequest)WebRequest.Create(url);
        request.Method = "POST";
        request.ContentType = "application/json";
        request.ContentLength = jsonPayload.Length;

        using (StreamWriter streamWriter = new StreamWriter(request.GetRequestStream()))
        {
            streamWriter.Write(jsonPayload);
        }

        try
        {
            using (HttpWebResponse response = (HttpWebResponse)request.GetResponse())
            using (Stream stream = response.GetResponseStream())
            using (StreamReader reader = new StreamReader(stream))
            {
                string responseFromServer = reader.ReadToEnd();
                Console.WriteLine(responseFromServer);
            }
        }
        catch (WebException ex)
        {
            HttpWebResponse errorResponse = (HttpWebResponse)ex.Response;
            using (Stream responseStream = errorResponse.GetResponseStream())
            using (StreamReader reader = new StreamReader(responseStream))
            {
                string errorResponseFromServer = reader.ReadToEnd();
                Console.WriteLine(errorResponseFromServer);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### Пример использования `HttpClient` для отправки POST-запроса:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Net.Http;
using System.Text;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

class Program
{
    static async Task Main()
    {
        string url = "http://example.com/api";
        string jsonPayload = "{\"name\":\"John\", \"age\":\"30\"}";

        using (HttpClient client = new HttpClient())
        {
            HttpContent content = new StringContent(jsonPayload, Encoding.UTF8, "application/json");

            try
            {
                HttpResponseMessage response = await client.PostAsync(url, content);
                response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
                string responseBody = await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync();
                Console.WriteLine(responseBody);
            }
            catch (HttpRequestException e)
            {
                Console.WriteLine("\nException Caught!");
                Console.WriteLine("Message :{0} ", e.Message);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Оба примера показывают, как отправлять POST-запросы в C#. `HttpClient` является более современным выбором, так как он встроен в .NET и предоставляет удобный API для работы с HTTP-запросами, а также имеет异шhtmlspecialcharshonый метод для асинхронной работы.

 Spring Security TextEncryptor接口主要处理文本加密和解密。它提供了一种标准化的方式来处理文本数据的加密和解密操作，确保敏感信息在网络传输和存储过程中的安全。

以下是TextEncryptor接口的一些主要功能和用途：

1. **加密文本**：将明文文本加密为密文文本。
2. **解密文本**：将密文文本解密回明文文本。
3. **提供加密密钥管理**：通常，TextEncryptor接口会依赖于某种加密密钥来执行加密和解密操作。密钥的安全管理是确保加密安全的关键。

在Spring Security中，TextEncryptor接口通常与其他组件一起使用，例如在配置自定义的安全策略时，用于对敏感数据进行加密。以下是一个简单的示例，展示了如何使用TextEncryptor接口进行文本加密和解密：

```java
import org.springframework.security.crypto.encrypt.TextEncryptor;

public class TextEncryptorExample {

    private final TextEncryptor textEncryptor;

    public TextEncryptorExample(String secret) {
        this.textEncryptor = new TextEncryptor() {
            private final String key = secret;

            @Override
            public String encrypt(String source) {
                // 简单的加密实现
                return source + key;
            }

            @Override
            public String decrypt(String source) {
                // 简单的解密实现
                return source.substring(0, source.length() - key.length());
            }
        };
    }

    public String encrypt(String plainText) {
        return textEncryptor.encrypt(plainText);
    }

    public String decrypt(String encryptedText) {
        return textEncryptor.decrypt(encryptedText);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        TextEncryptorExample example = new TextEncryptorExample("secret");

        String plainText = "Hello, World!";
        String encryptedText = example.encrypt(plainText);
        String decryptedText = example.decrypt(encryptedText);

        System.out.println("Plain Text: " + plainText);
        System.out.println("Encrypted Text: " + encryptedText);
        System.out.println("Decrypted Text: " + decryptedText);
    }
}
```

在这个示例中，`TextEncryptorExample`类实现了一个简单的TextEncryptor接口，用于加密和解密文本。实际应用中，开发者通常会使用更安全的加密算法和密钥管理机制。

