    uint immutable MY_CONSTANT;

    constructor(uint _myConstant) {
        MY_CONSTANT = _myConstant;
    }

    function getConstant() public view returns(uint) {
        return MY_CONSTANT;
    }
}
```

Для генерации целых чисел в функции `std::generate_n` you can use a lambda function that returns an integer. Here is an example:
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>

int main() {
  std::vector<int> vector(10);
  int i = 0;
  auto lambda = [&i]() -> int { return i++; };
  std::generate_n(vector.begin(), vector.size(), lambda);
  for (int n : vector) {
    std::cout << n << ' ';
  }
  return 0;
}
```

In this example, the lambda function returns the current value of `i` and then increments it. The type of the return value is `int`, which is the type of the elements in the vector.

